# SpaceLattice.aDNA — gitignore
# Written BEFORE first commit so private content never enters history.

# === LAYERED ARCHITECTURE: private layers ===
# what/local/ and how/local/ are operator/machine-specific by contract.
# Promotion to standard/ goes through skill_layer_promote (ADR-gated).
# Anything inside is ignored EXCEPT .example templates and READMEs which document
# the layer's structure for future operators.
/what/local/*
!/what/local/*.example
!/what/local/README.md
!/what/local/.gitkeep
/how/local/*
!/how/local/*.example
!/how/local/README.md
!/how/local/.gitkeep

# === DEPLOY RECEIPTS ===
# Deployment artifacts contain hostnames + machine state; per-machine, never published.
/deploy/

# === TELEMETRY OUTBOX / SENT (operator-local) ===
# Per-machine queued + sent telemetry. The maintainer-side aggregated inbox
# IS committed (audit trail) but the outbox/sent dirs stay local.
# _state.json tracks last-processed issue ID for idempotent re-runs (machine-local).
/who/peers/telemetry/outbox/
/who/peers/telemetry/sent/
/who/peers/telemetry/inbox/_state.json

# === PUBLISH ARTIFACTS ===
# skill_publish_lattice writes here; not committed to vault git.
/dist/
/.publish-clone/

# === SECRETS ===
# .example files (templates with placeholder values) ARE committed.
# Real secrets files never are.
secrets.env
.env
.env.local
*.secrets

# === PRIVATE ELISP ===
# Operator-private elisp lives in what/local/ but the convention is also
# enforced by suffix so accidental drift in standard/ gets caught.
*.private.el

# === CLAUDE CODE / AGENTIC TOOLING (per-session state) ===
# .claude/settings.json is project governance (hooks) — tracked.
# .claude/settings.local.json is operator-private — gitignored.
.claude/settings.local.json
.mcp.json

# === SCRATCH WORKTREES from skill_self_improve / skill_health_check ===
/tmp.dryrun-*/
*.dryrun-*

# === GENERATED CONTEXT GRAPH (regenerated on demand by adna-index-project) ===
/what/standard/index/graph.json

# === OBSIDIAN per-device state (already stripped at fork; ensure it stays gone) ===
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/graph.json
.obsidian/plugins/
.obsidian/themes/

# === STANDARD OS / LANGUAGE ARTIFACTS ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
.venv/
venv/
env/
node_modules/
.npm/
*.log
# But ADR dry-run logs are evidence — keep them tracked
!/what/decisions/adr/*.dryrun.log
*~
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# === EMACS BACKUP / AUTOSAVE ===
*~
\#*\#
.\#*
auto-save-list/
tramp/
.last_install.log
